definitions.definition: The Continental equivalent of the English pica : a measure of 12 Didot points (4.51368 mm or about 0.178 in .) or a body of type in this size .

main_definition: ( typography , Continental printing ) The Continental equivalent of the English pica : a measure of 12 Didot points (4.51368 mm or about 0.178 in .) or a body of type in this size .
